  "prompt": "How do I know who is following me on Snapchat?",
  "response": "To see who is following you on Snapchat, you can check your friends list and see who has added you. Here\u2019s how to do it:\n\n1. **Open Snapchat:** Launch the Snapchat app on your device.\n\n2. **Go to your Profile:** Tap on your Bitmoji or the profile icon at the top left corner of the screen.\n\n3. **Check Friends List:** \n   - Tap on \"My Friends.\" Here, you will see a list of all your friends on Snapchat. \n   - If someone has added you as a friend and you haven't added them back, they will also appear in this list.\n\n4. **Add Friends:** If you'd like to see who has added you but you haven't accepted their request, you can go to the \"Add Friends\" section by tapping on \"Add Friends\" under your profile. This will show you any pending requests.\n\n5. **Visibility of Followers:** Keep in mind that unlike some social media platforms, Snapchat does not have a dedicated \"followers\" section. The friends you see in your Friends List are those who can see your stories and send you snaps if you allow them to.\n\nIf you want to confirm new followers or recent friends, you can also look at your Snap Score, as it might change when new friends interact with your content. However, remember that Snapchat is designed to prioritize privacy, so it does not notify you when people follow you or view your profile.\n\nIf you have any specific privacy settings in place, you may want to review them to manage who can see your activities on the platform.",
